@Muhammad Seyan wasm is faster because you can compile c code for it, it runs in the same runtime as js. js isn't really slow, it's just that us js devs are generally not concerned with execution time, since it's hundreds/thousands of times faster than asset load times. 
the problem is only js has access to the DOM and media APIs. so js is the better compile target. and there are projects out there that offer compilation to a js subset and integrate the web apis. 
the only benefit for compiling to wasm(vs to js) is that you bypass garbage collection which is useful some c/c++ programs.
